The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 11 June is 42,623 (4,933.3 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 06 June, there were 252 new confirmed cases (29.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 30 May, there were 114 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 121% (138 extra cases).
